{
    "publish_date": "2013-07-17T15:02:52.000Z", 
    "video_length": "PT4M49S", 
    "captions": [
        {
            "text": "We live in a three-dimensional world", 
            "dur": "2.049", 
            "start": "11.702"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "where everything has length,", 
            "dur": "0.991", 
            "start": "13.751"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "width,", 
            "dur": "0.627", 
            "start": "14.742"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and height.", 
            "dur": "1.41", 
            "start": "15.369"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But what if our world were two-dimensional?", 
            "dur": "2.397", 
            "start": "16.779"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We would be squashed down", 
            "dur": "1.446", 
            "start": "19.176"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to occupy a single plane of existence,", 
            "dur": "2.512", 
            "start": "20.622"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "geometrically speaking, of course.", 
            "dur": "2.014", 
            "start": "23.134"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And what would that world look and feel like?", 
            "dur": "2.729", 
            "start": "25.148"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This is the premise", 
            "dur": "0.659", 
            "start": "27.877"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "of Edwin Abbott&#39;s 1884 novella, Flatland.", 
            "dur": "3.519", 
            "start": "28.536"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Flatland is a fun, mathematical thought experiment", 
            "dur": "2.267", 
            "start": "32.055"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that follows the trials and tribulations of a square", 
            "dur": "2.602", 
            "start": "34.322"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "exposed to the third dimension.", 
            "dur": "2.679", 
            "start": "36.924"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But what is a dimension, anyway?", 
            "dur": "2.38", 
            "start": "39.603"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "For our purposes, a dimension is a direction,", 
            "dur": "2.882", 
            "start": "41.983"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "which we can picture as a line.", 
            "dur": "2.262", 
            "start": "44.865"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "For our direction to be a dimension,", 
            "dur": "2.196", 
            "start": "47.127"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "it has to be at right angles to all other dimensions.", 
            "dur": "4.034", 
            "start": "49.323"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So, a one-dimensional space is just a line.", 
            "dur": "2.788", 
            "start": "53.357"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "A two-dimensional space is defined", 
            "dur": "1.805", 
            "start": "56.145"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "by two perpendicular lines,", 
            "dur": "2.155", 
            "start": "57.95"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "which describe a flat plane", 
            "dur": "1.57", 
            "start": "60.105"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "like a piece of paper.", 
            "dur": "1.636", 
            "start": "61.675"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And a three-dimensional space", 
            "dur": "1.317", 
            "start": "63.311"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "adds a third perpendicular line,", 
            "dur": "2.134", 
            "start": "64.628"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "which gives us height", 
            "dur": "1.282", 
            "start": "66.762"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and the world we&#39;re familiar with.", 
            "dur": "2.628", 
            "start": "68.044"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So, what about four dimensions?", 
            "dur": "1.824", 
            "start": "70.672"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And five?", 
            "dur": "0.982", 
            "start": "72.496"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And eleven?", 
            "dur": "1.117", 
            "start": "73.478"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Where do we put these new perpendicular lines?", 
            "dur": "2.71", 
            "start": "74.595"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This is where Flatland can help us.", 
            "dur": "2.535", 
            "start": "77.305"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Let&#39;s look at our square protagonist&#39;s world.", 
            "dur": "2.897", 
            "start": "79.84"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Flatland is populated by geometric shapes,", 
            "dur": "2.528", 
            "start": "82.737"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "ranging from isosceles trianges", 
            "dur": "1.668", 
            "start": "85.265"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to equilateral triangles", 
            "dur": "1.267", 
            "start": "86.933"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to squares,", 
            "dur": "0.789", 
            "start": "88.2"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "pentagons,", 
            "dur": "0.529", 
            "start": "88.989"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "hexagons,", 
            "dur": "0.595", 
            "start": "89.518"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "all the way up to circles.", 
            "dur": "2.155", 
            "start": "90.113"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "These shapes are all scurrying around a flat world,", 
            "dur": "2.763", 
            "start": "92.268"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "living their flat lives.", 
            "dur": "1.751", 
            "start": "95.031"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "They have a single eye on the front of their faces,", 
            "dur": "2.675", 
            "start": "96.782"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and let&#39;s see what the world looks like", 
            "dur": "1.083", 
            "start": "99.457"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "from their perspective.", 
            "dur": "1.916", 
            "start": "100.54"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "What they see is essentially one dimension,", 
            "dur": "2.892", 
            "start": "102.456"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "a line.", 
            "dur": "1.111", 
            "start": "105.348"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But in Abbott&#39;s Flatland,", 
            "dur": "1.387", 
            "start": "106.459"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "closer objects are brighter,", 
            "dur": "1.95", 
            "start": "107.846"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and that&#39;s how they see depth.", 
            "dur": "2.181", 
            "start": "109.796"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So a triangle looks different from a square,", 
            "dur": "2.332", 
            "start": "111.977"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "looks different a circle,", 
            "dur": "1.29", 
            "start": "114.309"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and so on.", 
            "dur": "1.299", 
            "start": "115.599"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Their brains cannot comprehend the third dimension.", 
            "dur": "2.613", 
            "start": "116.898"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In fact, they vehemently deny its existence", 
            "dur": "2.876", 
            "start": "119.511"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "because it&#39;s simply not part of their world", 
            "dur": "2.171", 
            "start": "122.387"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "or experience.", 
            "dur": "1.699", 
            "start": "124.558"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But all they need,", 
            "dur": "1.065", 
            "start": "126.257"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "as it turns out,", 
            "dur": "1.162", 
            "start": "127.322"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is a little boost.", 
            "dur": "2.114", 
            "start": "128.484"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "One day a sphere shows up in Flatland", 
            "dur": "1.918", 
            "start": "130.598"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to visit our square hero.", 
            "dur": "1.749", 
            "start": "132.516"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Here&#39;s what it looks like", 
            "dur": "0.937", 
            "start": "134.265"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "when the sphere passes through Flatland", 
            "dur": "2.147", 
            "start": "135.202"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "from the square&#39;s perspective,", 
            "dur": "2.516", 
            "start": "137.349"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and this blows his little square mind.", 
            "dur": "2.624", 
            "start": "139.865"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Then the sphere lifts the square", 
            "dur": "1.886", 
            "start": "142.489"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "into the third dimension,", 
            "dur": "1.538", 
            "start": "144.375"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the height direction where no Flatlander has gone before", 
            "dur": "3.049", 
            "start": "145.913"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and shows him his world.", 
            "dur": "2.005", 
            "start": "148.962"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "From up here, the square can see everything:", 
            "dur": "2.585", 
            "start": "150.967"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the shapes of buildings,", 
            "dur": "1.08", 
            "start": "153.552"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "all the precious gems hidden in the Earth,", 
            "dur": "2.141", 
            "start": "154.632"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and even the insides of his friends,", 
            "dur": "2.572", 
            "start": "156.773"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "which is probably pretty awkward.", 
            "dur": "2.672", 
            "start": "159.345"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Once the hapless square", 
            "dur": "1.122", 
            "start": "162.017"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "comes to terms with the third dimension,", 
            "dur": "1.753", 
            "start": "163.139"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "he begs his host to help him", 
            "dur": "1.388", 
            "start": "164.892"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "visit the fourth and higher dimensions,", 
            "dur": "2.241", 
            "start": "166.28"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "but the sphere bristles at the mere suggestion", 
            "dur": "2.126", 
            "start": "168.521"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "of dimensions higher than three", 
            "dur": "1.707", 
            "start": "170.647"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and exiles the square back to Flatland.", 
            "dur": "2.998", 
            "start": "172.354"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now, the sphere&#39;s indignation is understandable.", 
            "dur": "2.499", 
            "start": "175.352"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "A fourth dimension is very difficult", 
            "dur": "1.555", 
            "start": "177.851"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to reconcile with our experience of the world.", 
            "dur": "2.803", 
            "start": "179.406"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Short of being lifted into the fourth dimension", 
            "dur": "1.96", 
            "start": "182.209"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "by visiting hypercube,", 
            "dur": "1.413", 
            "start": "184.169"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "we can&#39;t experience it,", 
            "dur": "1.933", 
            "start": "185.582"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "but we can get close.", 
            "dur": "1.655", 
            "start": "187.515"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You&#39;ll recall that when the sphere", 
            "dur": "1.375", 
            "start": "189.17"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "first visited the second dimension,", 
            "dur": "1.919", 
            "start": "190.545"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "he looked like a series of circles", 
            "dur": "1.799", 
            "start": "192.464"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that started as a point", 
            "dur": "1.2", 
            "start": "194.263"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "when he touched Flatland,", 
            "dur": "1.418", 
            "start": "195.463"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "grew bigger until he was halfway through,", 
            "dur": "2.308", 
            "start": "196.881"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and then shrank smaller again.", 
            "dur": "1.997", 
            "start": "199.189"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We can think of this visit", 
            "dur": "1.33", 
            "start": "201.186"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "as a series of 2D cross-sections of a 3D object.", 
            "dur": "4.153", 
            "start": "202.516"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Well, we can do the same thing", 
            "dur": "1.421", 
            "start": "206.682"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "in the third dimension with a four-dimensional object.", 
            "dur": "4.117", 
            "start": "208.103"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Let&#39;s say that a hypersphere", 
            "dur": "1.204", 
            "start": "212.22"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is the 4D equivalent of a 3D sphere.", 
            "dur": "2.99", 
            "start": "213.424"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "When the 4D object passes through the third dimension,", 
            "dur": "2.911", 
            "start": "216.414"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "it&#39;ll look something like this.", 
            "dur": "2.607", 
            "start": "219.325"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Let&#39;s look at one more way", 
            "dur": "1.1", 
            "start": "221.932"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "of representing a four-dimensional object.", 
            "dur": "2.7", 
            "start": "223.032"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Let&#39;s say we have a point,", 
            "dur": "0.884", 
            "start": "225.732"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "a zero-dimensional shape.", 
            "dur": "2.078", 
            "start": "226.616"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now we extend it out one inch", 
            "dur": "1.542", 
            "start": "228.694"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and we have a one-dimensional line segment.", 
            "dur": "2.586", 
            "start": "230.236"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Extend the whole line segment by an inch,", 
            "dur": "2.09", 
            "start": "232.822"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and we get a 2D square.", 
            "dur": "2.158", 
            "start": "234.912"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Take the whole square and extend it out one inch,", 
            "dur": "2.176", 
            "start": "237.07"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and we get a 3D cube.", 
            "dur": "2.119", 
            "start": "239.246"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You can see where we&#39;re going with this.", 
            "dur": "1.65", 
            "start": "241.365"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Take the whole cube", 
            "dur": "1.162", 
            "start": "243.015"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and extend it out one inch,", 
            "dur": "1.356", 
            "start": "244.177"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "this time perpendicular to all three existing directions,", 
            "dur": "3.332", 
            "start": "245.533"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and we get a 4D hypercube,", 
            "dur": "2.393", 
            "start": "248.865"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "also called a tesseract.", 
            "dur": "2.568", 
            "start": "251.258"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "For all we know,", 
            "dur": "0.963", 
            "start": "253.826"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "there could be four-dimensional lifeforms", 
            "dur": "1.576", 
            "start": "254.789"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "somewhere out there,", 
            "dur": "1.253", 
            "start": "256.365"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "occasionally poking their heads", 
            "dur": "1.192", 
            "start": "257.618"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "into our bustling 3D world", 
            "dur": "2.148", 
            "start": "258.81"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and wondering what all the fuss is about.", 
            "dur": "2.187", 
            "start": "260.958"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In fact, there could be whole", 
            "dur": "1.166", 
            "start": "263.145"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "other four-dimensional worlds", 
            "dur": "1.77", 
            "start": "264.311"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "beyond our detection,", 
            "dur": "1.485", 
            "start": "266.081"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "hidden from us forever", 
            "dur": "1.003", 
            "start": "267.566"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "by the nature of our perception.", 
            "dur": "2.382", 
            "start": "268.569"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Doesn&#39;t that blow your little spherical mind?", 
            "dur": "3.252", 
            "start": "270.951"
        }
    ], 
